'''Edo San-Dai Matsuri''' (江戸三大祭り) refers to the three major traditional festivals held in Tokyo, Japan. 

The festivals are described with the phrase: '''"Mikoshi in Fukagawa, floats in Kanda, and spacious grounds for Sanno-sama."''' These festivals have been celebrated as annual events since the Edo period.

; {{ill|Kanda Matsuri|en|Kanda Matsuri|WD=Q218646|lt=Kanda Matsuri|1=Kanda Matsuri}}
: Held at [[Kanda Shrine]].
; [[Sanno Matsuri (Chiyoda-ku)|Sanno Matsuri]]
: Hosted by {{ill|Hie Shrine|en|Hie Shrine|WD=Q702042|lt=Hie Shrine|1=Hie Shrine}}.
; {{ill|Fukagawa Matsuri|en|Fukagawa Matsuri|WD=Q3090688|lt=Fukagawa Matsuri|1=Fukagawa Matsuri}}
: Celebrated at [[Tomioka Hachiman Shrine]].
